WEBVTT

00:15.015 --> 00:18.101
- Over there! It's the beast!
- Come on! Gather up!

00:22.522 --> 00:23.606
The beast!

00:28.028 --> 00:29.237
I can see him!

00:30.155 --> 00:32.157
- There! Go! Go!
- Go, go, go!

00:33.158 --> 00:34.743
Don't let him get away!

00:35.869 --> 00:36.911
Come on!

00:40.665 --> 00:42.500
You got him! You got him!

00:44.002 --> 00:45.128
Cut him off!

01:16.576 --> 01:19.037
Maybe we're hallucinating. I mean…

01:20.497 --> 01:23.082
Who knows what drugs
that doctor pumped us with?

01:23.083 --> 01:27.212
No. I swear I saw
that little blue-nosed monster talk.

01:30.048 --> 01:30.924
Hey!

01:33.218 --> 01:34.094
Say something.

01:37.180 --> 01:38.014
What are you?

01:40.433 --> 01:41.518
How old are you?

01:44.938 --> 01:46.147
Why won't you talk to us?

01:48.566 --> 01:50.317
See, I thought he was special.

01:50.318 --> 01:53.153
But if he's just a regular animal,
maybe we cook him up in a stew.

01:53.154 --> 01:54.321
Oh.

01:54.322 --> 01:57.449
Oh, Sanji. That is a great idea.

01:57.450 --> 02:00.495
With some onions, some carrots,

02:00.995 --> 02:02.622
some rosemary…

02:07.043 --> 02:09.045
Are you a bear or a person?

02:09.629 --> 02:12.924
I think he's a raccoon or something.
I mean, if raccoons could talk.

02:13.675 --> 02:16.219
Don't two legs and a top hat
make him a person?

02:16.719 --> 02:21.140
Yeah, but the antlers and the fur
kind of make it an animal.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.516
Can he be both?

02:22.517 --> 02:24.102
No. Evolutionary biology.

02:25.520 --> 02:26.938
Oh, hey!

02:28.356 --> 02:29.773
Whoa!

02:29.774 --> 02:31.651
Check this out!

02:32.152 --> 02:34.821
- Aw, cool pirate's flag.
- Leave that alone!

02:35.655 --> 02:39.159
Don't touch it! You hear me?
And I'm not a raccoon!

02:41.619 --> 02:43.163
I was a reindeer.

02:44.455 --> 02:46.166
You were right. He can talk.

02:48.918 --> 02:49.794
Huh.

02:57.385 --> 02:58.344
Hmm.

03:01.097 --> 03:04.349
This is the best meal I have ever had.

03:04.350 --> 03:05.309
What is this?

03:05.310 --> 03:06.811
It's just chicken soup.

03:07.729 --> 03:09.271
It's a classic medicinal recipe.

03:09.272 --> 03:12.108
Wanna stay here
and live in this huge castle, blondie?

03:13.193 --> 03:15.069
I'll make you my personal chef.

03:15.570 --> 03:16.571
Thanks.

03:17.322 --> 03:18.156
I'm good.

03:18.948 --> 03:20.158
Hey, doctor.

03:21.534 --> 03:23.368
- Why was that dog--
- You mean reindeer?

03:23.369 --> 03:24.703
You mean Chopper?

03:24.704 --> 03:27.165
Why did he get so angry
when I touched that flag?

03:27.999 --> 03:29.167
He didn't like it at all.

03:33.338 --> 03:34.505
That boy

03:36.466 --> 03:38.760
has a huge wound in his heart.

03:40.303 --> 03:42.263
Chopper's been alone his whole life.

03:42.764 --> 03:44.766
No family, no friends.

03:45.266 --> 03:49.687
Except for the worst doctor on the island,
who mattered a great deal to him.

03:50.563 --> 03:53.233
This was during the Great Doctor Hunt.

03:54.984 --> 03:59.821
<i>That tyrant Wapol was rounding up
all the doctors in Drum Kingdom</i>

03:59.822 --> 04:01.950
<i>and holding them hostage in his castle.</i>

04:02.450 --> 04:04.285
Let's head him off at the bridge!

04:05.662 --> 04:08.706
<i>If any MD resisted,</i>

04:09.666 --> 04:10.750
<i>they were killed.</i>

04:12.961 --> 04:17.507
<i>And soon, there were
just two free physicians left.</i>

04:18.800 --> 04:19.968
<i>Yours truly…</i>

04:20.468 --> 04:22.261
You gotta be kidding me.

04:22.262 --> 04:23.888
<i>…and Dr. Hiriluk.</i>

04:27.850 --> 04:28.893
Beat it.

04:29.394 --> 04:31.062
The Royal Guard is up there.

04:31.562 --> 04:33.021
I barely escaped.

04:33.022 --> 04:37.360
You think I'm under here for the view?
I'm trying to dodge those idiots too.

04:37.986 --> 04:40.238
I won't have you blowing up my spot.

04:42.323 --> 04:44.993
He went this way, men. Find him!

04:46.619 --> 04:48.621
Hurry up! Move!

04:54.127 --> 04:55.044
Come on!

04:57.922 --> 05:00.216
You know, we should be
looking out for each other.

05:00.925 --> 05:03.760
You and I are the only doctors
that Wapol hasn't captured.

05:03.761 --> 05:06.555
Yeah. If you can call yourself a doctor.

05:06.556 --> 05:09.933
Well, what do you call someone
who's trying to alleviate human suffering?

05:09.934 --> 05:11.644
Trying is right.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.563
I hear you turned
your last patient into a frog.

05:14.564 --> 05:15.897
Preposterous.

05:15.898 --> 05:19.026
This frog extract
is supposed to work on leg ailments.

05:19.027 --> 05:21.696
Should I have
administered it intravenously?

05:22.447 --> 05:24.573
This calls for another experiment.

05:24.574 --> 05:25.949
Yeah, good.

05:25.950 --> 05:28.410
You go and concoct
some more bizarre medicines

05:28.411 --> 05:30.037
that people find unwelcome.

05:30.038 --> 05:32.205
It's called a noble failure.

05:32.206 --> 05:34.291
All great scientists suffer them.

05:34.292 --> 05:36.626
Today's frog is tomorrow's prince.

05:36.627 --> 05:40.005
Only thing worse
than an incompetent physician

05:40.006 --> 05:41.298
is a bad scientist.

05:41.299 --> 05:44.719
You know, I don't need advice
from some greed-driven witch.

05:45.219 --> 05:46.678
Snake oil quack.

05:46.679 --> 05:47.972
Greedy old hag.

05:49.432 --> 05:51.725
- There!
- He went this way. Come on!

05:51.726 --> 05:53.561
That must be the Royal Guard.

05:54.562 --> 05:56.689
Or those townsfolk you love so much.

05:59.317 --> 06:00.735
Face it, Hiriluk.

06:01.402 --> 06:04.322
This country is sick, top to bottom.

06:04.989 --> 06:08.200
And these people are so desperate
without their doctors,

06:08.201 --> 06:11.079
they're scouring
the treacherous Valley of Death

06:11.662 --> 06:14.624
for some supposed cure-all mushroom.

06:16.334 --> 06:17.794
Cure-all mushroom.

06:18.336 --> 06:21.213
Not worth injury or death

06:21.214 --> 06:23.633
for something that doesn't even exist.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.804
There's a sucker born every minute.

06:28.805 --> 06:30.847
Could you not be so cruel?

06:30.848 --> 06:34.102
They only believe this stuff
because they have no hope.

06:34.852 --> 06:37.355
But I'm working on a cure

06:37.897 --> 06:39.440
that will save this country.

06:40.942 --> 06:43.027
It doesn't matter what you cook up.

06:44.320 --> 06:46.155
Drum Kingdom cannot be saved.

06:48.199 --> 06:49.575
You'll see.

06:50.201 --> 06:53.286
No sign of him here.
Men, circle back to the bridge.

06:53.287 --> 06:55.540
- Yes, sir!
- Well, that's my cue.

06:56.040 --> 06:58.126
They'll never catch me alive.

07:02.713 --> 07:04.506
See you around, old quack.

07:04.507 --> 07:07.135
Not if I see you first, you bag of bones.

07:16.185 --> 07:17.812
Safe at last.

07:19.355 --> 07:21.190
Idiots.

07:33.870 --> 07:36.497
Huge footprints.

07:40.501 --> 07:41.419
That turn into

07:42.503 --> 07:44.964
small footprints.

07:55.933 --> 07:57.310
Hello there.

07:59.103 --> 08:00.605
What's happened to you?

08:05.151 --> 08:06.443
You're in luck.

08:06.444 --> 08:07.528
Just last week,

08:08.488 --> 08:12.617
I created an ointment
that heals broken bones.

08:15.328 --> 08:17.163
You've been shot!

08:23.836 --> 08:24.837
All right.

08:25.588 --> 08:29.509
All right. All right.
It's all right. It's all right.

08:30.718 --> 08:31.636
Yes.

08:32.136 --> 08:33.386
Yes, it's okay.

08:33.387 --> 08:35.640
All right, sh, sh, sh, sh, sh.

08:36.265 --> 08:38.183
It's all right.

08:38.184 --> 08:40.061
Oh. Oh, okay. Okay.

08:40.561 --> 08:41.479
All right.

08:42.313 --> 08:44.899
No! If I don't
stop the bleeding, you'll die.

08:51.239 --> 08:52.323
It's okay.

08:52.949 --> 08:54.033
It's okay.

08:54.992 --> 08:56.577
I won't shoot you.

08:57.245 --> 09:01.123
I don't… I don't even have a gun. Look.

09:02.041 --> 09:03.750
Look.

09:03.751 --> 09:06.629
Nothing up my sleeves. No weapons at all.

09:10.299 --> 09:12.676
My name is Dr. Hiriluk.

09:12.677 --> 09:14.636
I'm a physician.

09:14.637 --> 09:16.430
I would never

09:17.098 --> 09:18.224
hurt you.

09:56.887 --> 09:57.763
Ah.

09:58.264 --> 09:59.348
Good afternoon.

10:00.474 --> 10:01.434
Good after…

10:01.934 --> 10:02.768
Shit.

10:05.688 --> 10:07.231
You can talk.

10:07.898 --> 10:09.442
And you have a potty mouth.

10:10.026 --> 10:11.277
Mm-mm.

10:12.612 --> 10:14.614
Why haven't you said anything before?

10:18.326 --> 10:19.535
Come on now.

10:20.578 --> 10:22.121
I don't judge.

10:25.583 --> 10:29.253
When I spoke to the other humans,
they shot at me.

10:29.879 --> 10:32.590
Because it's weird for a reindeer to talk.

10:36.385 --> 10:39.180
Yes, I've heard the villagers' tales about

10:39.805 --> 10:43.433
an abominable snowman
that lives in these woods.

10:43.434 --> 10:46.062
And I heard the gunfire last night.

10:48.898 --> 10:52.193
<i>You</i> must be the abominable snowman.

10:54.945 --> 10:58.491
Humankind can be so cruel.

11:01.869 --> 11:03.371
Do you mind if I, um,

11:04.080 --> 11:05.915
check your bandages?

11:06.916 --> 11:09.085
Let's look at that wound of yours.

11:09.585 --> 11:12.504
Hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm…

11:12.505 --> 11:15.006
What's an abominable snowman?

11:15.007 --> 11:15.925
A monster.

11:17.134 --> 11:19.929
Something you are not.

11:20.554 --> 11:22.014
All right.

11:23.849 --> 11:26.560
So what if you can talk?
It's nothing to brag about.

11:27.353 --> 11:28.938
I can talk too.

11:29.647 --> 11:31.273
Some people say I talk too much.

11:35.986 --> 11:38.447
Your injuries are healing just fine.

11:39.240 --> 11:41.117
As soon as they do,

11:41.951 --> 11:44.244
you can go home to your family.

11:44.245 --> 11:45.913
I don't have one.

11:46.414 --> 11:50.041
The other reindeer shun me
because of my blue nose.

11:50.042 --> 11:51.334
Oh.

11:51.335 --> 11:53.963
Humans aren't the only ones
who can be cruel.

11:55.172 --> 11:57.048
I can tell you this though.

11:57.049 --> 12:01.887
You are definitely one of a kind.

12:05.558 --> 12:06.641
So let's see.

12:06.642 --> 12:07.768
You were…

12:08.728 --> 12:11.354
You were born a reindeer, yes?

12:11.355 --> 12:12.690
Mm-hmm.

12:13.983 --> 12:15.234
Let me ask you something.

12:16.277 --> 12:19.613
Did you ever eat a strange-looking fruit?

12:20.656 --> 12:22.241
Something you probably shouldn't have?

12:23.784 --> 12:25.119
I was hungry.

12:26.328 --> 12:27.663
I think that's it.

12:28.664 --> 12:29.581
Huh?

12:29.582 --> 12:33.127
We have these things,
you see, called devil fruits.

12:33.836 --> 12:35.087
Very rare.

12:36.213 --> 12:39.132
I think that you ate one of those,

12:39.133 --> 12:41.677
and it turned you into…

12:45.055 --> 12:46.849
…what you are now.

12:50.478 --> 12:52.645
Mmm.

12:52.646 --> 12:54.440
Speaking of hungry.

12:55.316 --> 12:56.317
Hmm…

12:59.069 --> 13:00.070
Well…

13:02.573 --> 13:04.658
it isn't gourmet, but, uh…

13:10.664 --> 13:12.291
You like that, Chopper?

13:17.004 --> 13:18.088
Mm-hmm.

13:22.551 --> 13:24.595
Why did you call me Chopper?

13:25.221 --> 13:29.600
Because those antlers of yours
look like they could chop down trees.

13:33.270 --> 13:35.314
Tony Tony Chopper.

13:36.857 --> 13:38.067
That's a good name.

13:38.943 --> 13:40.486
That's what I'm gonna call you.

13:42.905 --> 13:44.031
Chopper.

13:45.699 --> 13:46.700
I like it.

13:53.082 --> 13:53.999
Thank you.

13:56.168 --> 13:58.879
It's my extreme pleasure.

14:04.927 --> 14:05.845
<i>Chopper</i>

14:06.720 --> 14:08.764
spent the next year with Hiriluk.

14:11.725 --> 14:13.060
Precedes the first…

14:17.231 --> 14:18.566
<i>Working with him.</i>

14:20.150 --> 14:22.152
<i>Learning from him.</i>

14:22.862 --> 14:24.738
<i>Healing from his wounds.</i>

14:25.614 --> 14:28.825
<i>They were like two awkward peas in a pod.</i>

14:28.826 --> 14:31.286
<i>But like any relationship,</i>

14:31.287 --> 14:33.122
<i>they had their blow-ups.</i>

14:40.212 --> 14:43.048
- That could have killed me!
- What are you talking about?

14:43.632 --> 14:49.138
I saved your life. Why would I try
to kill you now, you blue-nosed fool?

14:50.264 --> 14:52.266
Don't call me a blue-nosed fool!

14:54.894 --> 14:55.853
Stop.

15:24.381 --> 15:25.341
Um…

15:27.384 --> 15:28.552
Doctor?

15:29.345 --> 15:30.346
What?

15:33.223 --> 15:35.142
This is my first fight.

15:47.404 --> 15:49.156
Well, it's no wonder.

15:51.992 --> 15:54.662
You need a partner to fight.

15:57.081 --> 15:58.082
Well,

15:59.249 --> 16:02.294
this is probably going to be
a first for you too.

16:17.518 --> 16:18.519
Here.

16:19.103 --> 16:20.521
Here's, um,

16:21.522 --> 16:24.733
a little something for you.

16:31.573 --> 16:33.283
A peace offering.

16:53.929 --> 16:55.305
Thank you.

17:00.185 --> 17:01.311
You're welcome.

17:04.398 --> 17:05.399
Right.

17:12.614 --> 17:14.700
Cross your hooves, Chopper.

17:23.751 --> 17:25.376
It's blown up ten times.

17:25.377 --> 17:27.087
Why do we keep trying?

17:28.714 --> 17:32.925
Because once my miracle cure is perfected,

17:32.926 --> 17:35.720
this country is as good as saved.

17:35.721 --> 17:37.638
You want to save the people?

17:37.639 --> 17:40.725
The people who shoot abominable snowmen?

17:40.726 --> 17:41.602
And me?

17:43.228 --> 17:44.729
Listen to me, Chopper.

17:44.730 --> 17:46.774
Don't hold a grudge.

17:47.733 --> 17:50.318
After years of living
under a cruel tyrant,

17:50.319 --> 17:52.321
the people of Drum are broken.

17:53.864 --> 17:56.950
They've given up hope
that things can change for the better.

17:57.743 --> 17:59.787
And once people lose hope,

18:00.454 --> 18:03.873
they give in to fear
and shoot at monsters.

18:03.874 --> 18:06.001
And Choppers.

18:08.337 --> 18:11.131
We need to give them their hope back.

18:12.424 --> 18:13.758
How do we do that?

18:13.759 --> 18:15.552
We never give up on them.

18:17.971 --> 18:19.473
Or this.

18:23.644 --> 18:26.355
In a faraway land in the west,

18:27.648 --> 18:29.566
there was a famous robber

18:30.359 --> 18:32.319
with a serious heart problem.

18:33.821 --> 18:36.322
And fortunately, he was rich,

18:36.323 --> 18:40.535
and so he sought out famous physicians
from far and wide,

18:40.536 --> 18:42.121
but none of them

18:43.122 --> 18:45.249
could cure his disease.

18:46.166 --> 18:47.458
None?

18:47.459 --> 18:50.796
It was incurable.

18:53.215 --> 18:54.132
Oh.

18:54.133 --> 18:57.678
And then one day,
in the midst of his despair,

18:58.929 --> 19:01.306
after he nearly went mad,

19:02.474 --> 19:04.517
he was passing a mountain,

19:04.518 --> 19:07.354
and there he saw a sight…

19:09.898 --> 19:11.817
that took his breath away.

19:13.777 --> 19:15.028
What was it?

19:17.823 --> 19:19.449
Cherry blossoms.

19:20.325 --> 19:21.660
Oh.

19:22.953 --> 19:25.122
He'd never seen anything so…

19:26.331 --> 19:28.167
So beautiful?

19:34.965 --> 19:36.592
Well, the very next day,

19:38.135 --> 19:40.846
the robber went to see yet another doctor,

19:41.346 --> 19:45.976
and to his utter surprise,
the physician told him that he was

19:47.019 --> 19:48.145
cured.

19:49.062 --> 19:50.104
Oh.

19:50.105 --> 19:50.939
It was…

19:52.983 --> 19:53.984
It was…

19:54.985 --> 19:56.028
A miracle?

19:56.528 --> 19:58.863
A miracle!

19:58.864 --> 19:59.907
Yes.

20:00.407 --> 20:02.783
A medical marvel.

20:02.784 --> 20:06.955
You see, the powerful emotion

20:07.539 --> 20:10.334
that he experienced from looking

20:11.376 --> 20:13.545
at cherry blossoms

20:14.546 --> 20:15.839
had healed him.

20:16.840 --> 20:18.300
Wow.

20:21.845 --> 20:22.930
Look here.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.684
This flag, it's a symbol of conviction.

20:28.268 --> 20:32.146
It means that nothing is impossible.

20:32.147 --> 20:37.110
It means there's no such thing
as an incurable disease.

20:37.694 --> 20:42.448
I will be the doctor
that saves this sick country.

20:42.449 --> 20:45.034
That's why I hoist
the skull and crossbones

20:45.035 --> 20:47.246
against any disease there is.

20:48.330 --> 20:50.039
Skull and crossbones?

20:50.040 --> 20:51.166
Yes!

20:52.125 --> 20:54.419
A symbol of faith.

20:54.920 --> 20:58.465
A rejection of impossibilities.

20:59.007 --> 21:01.217
Hoist this flag

21:01.218 --> 21:04.763
and fight like a pirate!

21:06.890 --> 21:08.015
Mmm…

21:08.016 --> 21:09.393
What's a pirate?

21:13.230 --> 21:14.398
Really?

21:16.692 --> 21:22.572
A pirate is someone who has adventures and

21:24.116 --> 21:25.492
dreams

21:27.327 --> 21:32.082
and never, ever gives up.

21:34.334 --> 21:39.423
Oh, Chopper, this island
is but a tiny speck

21:39.923 --> 21:42.301
in a world beyond imagining.

21:44.428 --> 21:45.511
Really?

21:45.512 --> 21:48.056
Set sail one day,

21:49.391 --> 21:53.020
and you'll discover
just how small your problems really are.

21:56.315 --> 21:58.817
Mark my words, my boy…

22:01.069 --> 22:02.487
your destiny

22:03.655 --> 22:06.783
lies beyond that shining sea.

22:14.791 --> 22:16.710
<i>But the good times didn't last.</i>

22:20.797 --> 22:22.549
<i>They rarely do.</i>

22:25.218 --> 22:32.141
And in other news, Chopper, I'm happy
to say your treatment is finally complete.

22:32.142 --> 22:34.060
Really?

22:34.061 --> 22:35.520
Thank you, Doctor.

22:37.272 --> 22:39.524
Well, uh…

22:42.319 --> 22:43.653
Take care of yourself.

22:46.907 --> 22:48.408
You're free to go.

22:49.785 --> 22:50.660
Huh?

22:54.247 --> 22:57.333
Your… your… your wounds have healed.

22:57.334 --> 22:58.877
You're free to

22:59.419 --> 23:01.671
live your life any way you want.

23:05.384 --> 23:07.552
Now go! I have work to do.

23:08.512 --> 23:10.013
But…

23:10.514 --> 23:11.722
but I'm not healed!

23:11.723 --> 23:13.766
I… have a stomachache.

23:13.767 --> 23:14.893
I have a fever.

23:15.727 --> 23:18.063
- I think my antlers are breaking!
- You're fine.

23:20.482 --> 23:22.817
I don't have to keep looking after you
any longer, Chopper.

23:22.818 --> 23:25.237
You can take care of yourself.

23:25.862 --> 23:27.696
Please don't do this, Doctor.

23:27.697 --> 23:31.158
I don't have any friends.
I don't have anywhere else to go.

23:31.159 --> 23:33.202
I promise I won't be any trouble, I swear.

23:33.203 --> 23:34.287
Go away!

23:35.539 --> 23:38.625
Take to the seas or something,
and never come back!

23:39.209 --> 23:41.377
But… but--

23:41.378 --> 23:42.963
I'm done with you!

23:43.797 --> 23:45.424
You blue-nosed fool!

23:55.016 --> 23:56.726
No! Why?

23:57.811 --> 23:59.229
Doctor, why?

23:59.813 --> 24:01.398
What did I do?

24:02.274 --> 24:03.566
Doctor!

24:03.567 --> 24:07.737
Doctor, please! Please.
Please open the door, Doctor!

24:08.572 --> 24:10.531
Doctor, what did I do?

24:10.532 --> 24:13.368
Please open the door, Doctor! Please!

24:13.869 --> 24:17.414
Doctor! Doctor! Please!

24:17.956 --> 24:19.331
What did I do?

24:19.332 --> 24:20.916
Forgive me.

24:20.917 --> 24:23.170
Forgive me, Chopper.

24:24.254 --> 24:25.172
No.

24:26.131 --> 24:27.215
No!

25:00.999 --> 25:02.209
Chopper.

25:04.711 --> 25:06.213
No wonder it doesn't like humans.

25:09.007 --> 25:11.510
If you ask me, it's his best quality.

25:13.470 --> 25:16.723
Chopper and Hiriluk's story
didn't end there.

25:35.992 --> 25:37.953
- You're a goner.
- No.

25:38.954 --> 25:40.037
No.

25:40.038 --> 25:41.331
There must be

25:41.831 --> 25:46.461
some way to prolong my life
just a little bit longer.

25:47.754 --> 25:49.714
Use your skills!

25:53.260 --> 25:54.469
So you admit it.

25:54.970 --> 25:57.930
I am not just a greed-driven witch.

25:57.931 --> 25:59.515
I've got skills.

25:59.516 --> 26:01.309
And you're the only other doctor left.

26:03.270 --> 26:04.854
I can't

26:05.730 --> 26:07.274
bear to see

26:08.149 --> 26:11.235
30 years of research go to waste.

26:11.236 --> 26:14.822
I need more time to finish my life's work.

26:14.823 --> 26:18.326
So go back to that land
where you saw those cherry blossoms.

26:18.868 --> 26:21.662
I know you don't believe me, but I exper…

26:21.663 --> 26:25.457
I experienced a medical marvel.

26:25.458 --> 26:27.627
You're gonna need another one.

26:28.128 --> 26:31.839
The… the cure-all mushroom
the villagers talk about--

26:31.840 --> 26:33.216
Doesn't exist.

26:34.009 --> 26:35.426
And even if it did,

26:35.427 --> 26:38.722
nobody gets out
of the Valley of Death alive.

26:47.022 --> 26:48.732
Where's your pet?

26:50.942 --> 26:53.612
Chopper's not a pet!

26:55.822 --> 26:57.949
I'm the only friend he's ever known.

26:58.700 --> 27:00.452
That's…

27:00.952 --> 27:03.955
That's why I had to kick him out.

27:04.456 --> 27:05.373
What?

27:05.874 --> 27:06.916
Why?

27:08.001 --> 27:10.629
It would be an unbearable shock

27:11.755 --> 27:14.174
if I died right in front of his eyes.

27:14.841 --> 27:17.302
I had to spare him that. We're, uh…

27:19.179 --> 27:21.138
We're a lot alike, he and I.

27:21.139 --> 27:22.806
You're both clumsy.

27:22.807 --> 27:23.933
I wanted to

27:25.060 --> 27:27.604
give him one last present.

27:28.438 --> 27:34.986
One last thing
to show him that nothing is impossible.

27:35.612 --> 27:36.571
But…

27:38.365 --> 27:40.617
I know time

27:42.243 --> 27:44.204
is not on my side.

27:47.624 --> 27:48.792
Kureha.

27:54.422 --> 27:55.674
Please.

28:00.720 --> 28:01.888
Please…

28:03.890 --> 28:05.934
finish my life's work.

28:06.643 --> 28:07.560
And…

28:09.479 --> 28:11.231
take care of Chopper.

28:13.692 --> 28:14.734
Get up.

28:15.860 --> 28:19.947
You seriously expect me
to finish your foolish research

28:19.948 --> 28:21.533
and look after your weird pet?

28:22.951 --> 28:26.162
You are trying to play on my sympathies
because you're dying.

28:27.080 --> 28:28.748
You should know me better than that.

28:29.249 --> 28:30.792
The answer is no.

28:38.258 --> 28:41.010
Get your affairs in order, old quack.

28:49.477 --> 28:52.563
Knowing his time was short,

28:52.564 --> 28:56.901
Hiriluk worked feverishly
those last few days.

29:10.081 --> 29:13.000
I'll show you what is possible.
I'll show you!

29:13.001 --> 29:15.170
Oh God.

29:45.742 --> 29:46.868
It's working.

29:52.123 --> 29:53.291
It's working!

29:53.792 --> 29:54.667
Ah!

29:58.505 --> 30:00.131
Oh! Oh!

30:00.799 --> 30:01.758
Oh!

30:03.134 --> 30:04.344
Chopper, this is it!

30:06.221 --> 30:08.765
The reaction we've been waiting for!

30:10.391 --> 30:11.267
Ah!

30:14.145 --> 30:15.646
Aha!

30:15.647 --> 30:16.523
Ah!

30:17.690 --> 30:18.858
Chopper!

30:19.359 --> 30:20.235
Chop…

30:56.938 --> 30:58.940
I… got it.

31:01.317 --> 31:02.318
Chopper?

31:06.155 --> 31:07.323
Chopper, what…

31:12.871 --> 31:16.040
What in the hell
has happened to you? What…

31:17.834 --> 31:18.960
Chopper…

31:19.460 --> 31:21.087
Where have you been?

31:21.921 --> 31:23.715
The Valley of Death.

31:24.215 --> 31:26.008
I found the mushroom.

31:26.009 --> 31:27.427
What? The, uh…

31:29.387 --> 31:32.515
The cure-all the villagers
have been talking about?

31:33.099 --> 31:34.225
Uh-huh.

31:35.018 --> 31:36.019
What…

31:38.021 --> 31:40.273
You found it.

31:41.774 --> 31:43.067
For me.

31:43.902 --> 31:47.654
Live, Doctor, please.

31:47.655 --> 31:49.948
I want to become a doctor too.

31:49.949 --> 31:52.577
And I want you to be my first patient.

31:53.745 --> 31:55.538
Teach me how to be one.

31:56.873 --> 32:00.293
Or can't a reindeer be a doctor?

32:09.802 --> 32:11.930
Of course you can, Chopper.

32:15.892 --> 32:19.646
You've got
the most important qualification.

32:21.981 --> 32:24.317
A big heart.

32:29.405 --> 32:30.823
Oh, my boy, my boy.

32:57.433 --> 32:58.810
Ah.

33:00.812 --> 33:02.522
Is the mushroom soup working?

33:04.107 --> 33:05.274
It was terrible.

33:08.069 --> 33:11.239
Good medicine always tastes bad.

33:12.407 --> 33:14.492
That's how you know it's working.

33:17.161 --> 33:19.955
Thank you, Chopper.
Now I must take my leave.

33:19.956 --> 33:21.289
Where are you going?

33:21.290 --> 33:22.375
Well, Chopper,

33:22.875 --> 33:27.421
I've gotten word
that the doctors being held at Drum Castle

33:27.422 --> 33:29.048
have fallen ill.

33:30.049 --> 33:31.801
Now that I'm better,

33:32.427 --> 33:34.303
I'm going to heal them.

33:38.141 --> 33:39.392
Hmm?

33:46.107 --> 33:47.525
Is that medicine?

33:48.693 --> 33:50.111
Explosives.

33:51.487 --> 33:54.115
The castle is heavily guarded.

33:54.907 --> 33:56.492
I may have to

33:57.452 --> 33:59.203
fight my way in.

34:07.170 --> 34:08.713
I'll come with you.

34:09.672 --> 34:12.425
No, no. You're in worse shape than I am.

34:12.967 --> 34:14.677
You stay here and rest.

34:24.312 --> 34:26.939
You're going to make a fine doctor
one day, Chopper.

34:28.649 --> 34:31.778
I'm living proof of that.

34:47.960 --> 34:49.045
Hiriluk!

34:50.421 --> 34:51.506
Where is he?

34:52.006 --> 34:56.051
Now that he's better, he's gone to heal
the sick doctors in the castle.

34:56.052 --> 34:56.969
Better?

34:57.553 --> 35:00.765
He's not better. His disease is incurable.

35:01.349 --> 35:02.557
No, really.

35:02.558 --> 35:06.269
I found the cure-all mushroom
from the book and made him some soup.

35:06.270 --> 35:08.022
What mushroom? Show me.

35:13.361 --> 35:14.487
See?

35:15.446 --> 35:18.825
The skull and crossbones
means anything is possible.

35:19.700 --> 35:21.702
Any disease can be cured.

35:27.291 --> 35:29.251
You idiot!

35:29.252 --> 35:32.420
That symbol means it's lethal.

35:32.421 --> 35:35.258
Whoever eats that mushroom
dies within the hour.

35:37.468 --> 35:39.095
You're lying!

35:39.846 --> 35:41.721
I do not lie.

35:41.722 --> 35:45.434
He knew it was poisonous.
He drank it anyway.

35:48.062 --> 35:49.229
Why would he do that?

35:49.230 --> 35:52.149
Because he had a soft spot for you

35:52.150 --> 35:55.570
in his misguided, oversized heart.

36:00.032 --> 36:02.701
There is no such thing as a cure-all.

36:02.702 --> 36:05.954
That's why doctors are needed.

36:05.955 --> 36:08.833
Kindness does not save lives.

36:09.333 --> 36:14.338
If you really wanna save people,
you need to study and learn medicine.

36:15.298 --> 36:17.716
Because without those skills,

36:17.717 --> 36:20.219
you will not save a single person.

36:27.476 --> 36:29.645
But Doctor said…

36:30.980 --> 36:32.023
That fool.

36:39.864 --> 36:41.949
Dr. Hiriluk won't be back.

36:49.248 --> 36:52.418
He's gone to make Drum Castle his grave.

37:12.939 --> 37:15.148
<i>To my dying breath…</i>

37:15.149 --> 37:17.692
No!

37:17.693 --> 37:19.946
<i>…I shall do all within my power</i>

37:21.113 --> 37:23.991
<i>to ease the suffering of the sick.</i>

37:25.368 --> 37:28.120
No!

37:30.998 --> 37:33.918
Stay strong, fellow physicians.

37:35.378 --> 37:37.004
I've come to save you.

37:50.268 --> 37:53.520
We need to continue
monitoring your health, my king.

37:53.521 --> 37:56.856
With your insatiable royal appetite,

37:56.857 --> 38:00.820
I shudder to think what would
become of Drum were you to fall ill.

38:01.320 --> 38:03.947
While your due diligence is commendable,

38:03.948 --> 38:05.741
your concern is misplaced.

38:06.242 --> 38:07.827
I'm as fit as a fiddle.

38:09.453 --> 38:11.789
I'm strong as an ox.

38:12.456 --> 38:13.749
Ow!

38:14.750 --> 38:16.584
It's too tight.

38:16.585 --> 38:18.296
Forgive me, King Wapol.

38:20.381 --> 38:22.383
- Take this one away.
- Yes, sire.

38:22.883 --> 38:25.969
And see that he is severely punished

38:25.970 --> 38:30.265
for nearly disfiguring the royal physique.

38:30.266 --> 38:31.600
My liege.

38:32.184 --> 38:33.269
My liege.

38:34.770 --> 38:37.231
The fugitive doctor has arrived.

38:43.070 --> 38:45.031
Take me to the patients!

38:55.666 --> 39:00.379
I have come to heal the sick doctors.

39:07.928 --> 39:08.846
Sick?

39:10.139 --> 39:12.558
As you can see, no one here is sick.

39:20.608 --> 39:22.026
Thank goodness.

39:26.113 --> 39:29.116
It was just me being tricked.

39:37.333 --> 39:39.752
Can you believe this buffoon?

39:40.252 --> 39:42.630
I thought you had to be smart
to be a physician.

39:46.592 --> 39:49.636
I order the immediate execution

39:49.637 --> 39:51.722
of this fugitive doctor.

40:02.942 --> 40:04.193
Knowing the danger,

40:06.153 --> 40:07.320
why did you come?

40:07.321 --> 40:09.031
I am a doctor.

40:09.573 --> 40:11.200
If someone is sick,

40:11.700 --> 40:13.369
I'm going to try to treat them.

40:14.578 --> 40:16.913
If this were an emergency,

40:16.914 --> 40:20.209
I wouldn't call for a quack like you.

40:21.085 --> 40:22.002
Dalton!

40:23.003 --> 40:24.839
Shoot the rebel dead.

40:37.476 --> 40:39.186
You can't kill me.

40:46.527 --> 40:49.530
When does a man die?

40:51.991 --> 40:55.661
Is it when a bullet pierces his heart?

40:57.204 --> 41:00.958
Or he's stricken by an incurable disease?

41:02.209 --> 41:03.043
No.

41:04.336 --> 41:05.504
<i>Is it when</i>

41:06.797 --> 41:10.384
<i>he eats soup
made from a poisonous mushroom?</i>

41:12.803 --> 41:14.721
<i>No. No, no, no.</i>

41:14.722 --> 41:16.599
No. No!

41:18.100 --> 41:20.644
A man dies

41:21.854 --> 41:23.731
when he is forgotten.

41:26.150 --> 41:28.194
I may disappear,

41:29.403 --> 41:31.655
<i>but my dream</i>

41:32.239 --> 41:33.741
<i>will live on!</i>

41:35.701 --> 41:40.623
And the ailing people of Drum
will be healed.

41:44.126 --> 41:46.170
Is it true for a country as well?

41:49.048 --> 41:50.591
Can Drum Kingdom

41:51.217 --> 41:52.384
be saved?

41:54.094 --> 41:56.597
As long as there is someone
to carry it on.

41:58.307 --> 42:00.683
What are you blabbering about?

42:00.684 --> 42:01.685
Shoot him!

42:05.272 --> 42:06.357
Soon…

42:08.609 --> 42:10.569
a monster will appear.

42:13.781 --> 42:15.157
Please don't hurt him.

42:17.034 --> 42:18.786
He is my son.

42:26.752 --> 42:28.045
I've had

42:29.171 --> 42:31.840
a marvelous life.

42:33.092 --> 42:36.011
Shoot him!

42:40.683 --> 42:42.309
Thank you, Chopper.

42:52.861 --> 42:54.280
Here's to you, old quack.

43:15.634 --> 43:18.178
What a damn fool!

43:21.724 --> 43:22.725
Go!

43:23.225 --> 43:24.560
Now!

43:26.478 --> 43:29.523
Kill the monster son!

44:00.387 --> 44:04.016
No!

44:28.165 --> 44:29.124
Move!

44:30.668 --> 44:34.088
If you can't beat me,
you won't stand a chance against them.

44:36.882 --> 44:39.885
Don't sacrifice yourself needlessly
for this country.

44:41.220 --> 44:42.429
Live.

44:43.180 --> 44:44.056
Please.

44:44.932 --> 44:45.766
Go home.

44:46.934 --> 44:49.103
Your father would want that.

45:22.886 --> 45:24.847
Where is the beast?

45:25.347 --> 45:27.390
Did you not bring me his head?

45:27.391 --> 45:29.560
I have turned a blind eye

45:30.561 --> 45:32.146
for a long time.

45:33.272 --> 45:35.189
I served your father,

45:35.190 --> 45:37.860
but now I see
where this country is headed.

45:41.613 --> 45:42.906
Collapse.

45:44.324 --> 45:48.203
And I won't walk that path any longer.

45:59.006 --> 46:00.591
You defy me?

46:01.675 --> 46:02.843
Me?!

46:03.719 --> 46:05.304
Your king?!

46:08.557 --> 46:09.683
I do.

46:12.478 --> 46:15.314
Take this traitor in!

46:35.959 --> 46:37.169
Interesting.

46:47.346 --> 46:48.764
What are you doing?

47:14.039 --> 47:15.916
I'm gonna become a doctor.

47:22.256 --> 47:23.674
I will become a doctor.

47:24.258 --> 47:26.801
I will become
a cure-all for every disease.

47:26.802 --> 47:28.302
I won't give up.

47:28.303 --> 47:29.429
Please.

47:30.806 --> 47:32.975
Please teach me everything you know.

47:36.562 --> 47:39.147
Why would I do that?

48:03.630 --> 48:04.631
Hmm.

48:06.174 --> 48:08.093
Call me "Doctorine."

48:49.885 --> 48:51.011
Where's he going?

49:11.740 --> 49:13.200
Morning, fellas.

49:17.245 --> 49:18.747
Nothing from Luffy.

49:20.332 --> 49:23.085
- Not yet.
- We should head up the path.

49:25.295 --> 49:26.672
Yeah.

49:31.343 --> 49:33.637
Hey, I'm sorry for snapping last night.

49:36.974 --> 49:40.018
Just the pressure
getting to me too, I guess.

49:45.565 --> 49:47.317
But I brought you breakfast.

49:52.781 --> 49:53.740
We're cool.

49:57.703 --> 49:58.704
What is it?

50:00.205 --> 50:01.248
Smoke.

50:02.541 --> 50:03.709
From a campfire.

50:05.377 --> 50:06.586
Didn't see any boats coming in.

50:08.005 --> 50:09.006
I'll investigate.

50:10.132 --> 50:11.633
- I'll join.
- No.

50:13.301 --> 50:15.512
Stay. Please.

50:18.265 --> 50:20.434
It could be nothing. But…

50:23.103 --> 50:26.940
If you have the trust
of the Princess of Alabasta, then…

50:30.235 --> 50:31.945
perhaps I can trust you as well.

50:36.199 --> 50:37.325
You knew about Vivi?

50:38.410 --> 50:39.703
Not at first.

50:41.204 --> 50:42.581
We'd met before.

50:43.999 --> 50:45.459
A long time ago.

50:48.086 --> 50:50.047
She is a very impressive young woman.

50:53.759 --> 50:54.593
We'll stay.

51:09.524 --> 51:12.526
Did you just volunteer
to be acting Captain of the Guard?

51:12.527 --> 51:14.154
You did tell me to do something.

51:30.837 --> 51:31.838
Hmm.

51:38.720 --> 51:39.678
Hey!

51:39.679 --> 51:41.848
I told you not to touch that.

51:48.688 --> 51:51.233
I respect all pirate flags.

51:52.567 --> 51:54.861
It shouldn't just be sitting
inside some box.

51:57.072 --> 51:58.281
It should be hung.

51:59.116 --> 52:00.117
Proudly.

52:07.207 --> 52:08.708
Especially this one.

52:23.431 --> 52:25.433
Let's put it where it belongs.

52:42.951 --> 52:44.536
Oh, shit.

52:45.620 --> 52:46.663
Yeah.

52:48.290 --> 52:49.583
I'm a monster too.

52:53.795 --> 52:55.046
Isn't it great?

54:12.457 --> 54:14.376
The traitor lives.

54:15.377 --> 54:16.586
Not for long.
